Part 1: Live Greeting App — quick, smooth, and hella satisfying.

🧠 Live Greeting App
🎯 Goal:
User types their name → It instantly says:

"Hello, [Name]!" on the screen.

✅ Step-by-step:
🔸 HTML

<input type="text" id="nameInput" placeholder="Enter your name" />
<p id="greetingText">👋 Type your name above</p>
  
🔸 JavaScript

document.getElementById("nameInput").addEventListener("input", function () {
  let name = document.getElementById("nameInput").value;
  document.getElementById("greetingText").innerText = "Hello, " + name + "!";
});

💡 How it works:
addEventListener("input", ...): Fires every time you type
Grabs the value of the input
Sets it as the new greeting in real-time using .innerText

✅ What is innerText?
It means: "Get or set the text inside an HTML element."

🔍 Example:

HTML:
<p id="demo">Hello!</p>
  
JavaScript:
// Read the text
let text = document.getElementById("demo").innerText;
console.log(text); // ➜ "Hello!"
// Change the text
document.getElementById("demo").innerText = "Yo, Navnit!";

🧠 Use it when you want to:

Display output on the page
Update messages, labels, scores, etc.
React to user actions by changing visible content

✅ TL;DR:
innerText = "change what the user sees inside a tag"

***DOM stands for: Document Object Model***
